I have literally just finished reading Sword of Destiny by Andrzej Sapkowski.
.
Rating 3.5/5 â­
.
I wasn't a massive fan of the first few short stories but as it progressed I think they got better. I loved the introduction to Ciri and tying up the threads about her that started in the first book. 
As well as revisiting other characters a few years on like Yennefer and Dandelion.
.
I love the characters in this series so far. They've got so much personality, especially 10 year old Ciri. I was suprised by how bold and yet still so childlike she is. Dandelion is still a favourite of mine. I love a funny side character that is almost a nuisance to the protagonist but also a sweetheart and he fits the part perfectly.
.
This series seems to be big on exploring themes about humanity and nature too, especially through Geralt and the many conflicts he faces. I think that's a massive strength to this series, the fact that's it's a fun monster hunting fantasy but it also goes very deep and dark. If you're a big theme and character driven reader, then I would definitely check this series out.
.
Also shout out to this book for making me want to watch the show again. I will never watch anything new because I just revisit shows constantly. On that note, what's your go to TV show that you can watch over and over?
. 
Mines absolutely Merlin and now Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood. I can't count how many times I've watched Merlin.
.
I'm off to London for a few days, tomorrow. I will probably still be active but not as much as usual.
Have a good dayâ¤
.
